Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of orthographic features in online communication, specifically on Twitter, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The focus on emoticons and emojis suggests a sub-category of NLP related to sentiment analysis and paralinguistic communication, which is covered in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of causal inference methods suggests a sub-category related to machine learning and statistics, which could be covered in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The study of online communication and social media could also fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
